ht and saw a slaughterhouse that they called stock medium. I was watching from the stands, but my goodness, I thought someone was going to get killed. As i wasnt on the track and cant see every kart 100% of the time, i did see a #21 kart start it all. I'm not sure who it was, I have seen him there before in medium and he has won some and he drives the same way every week. He is an absolute maniac. If i raced that class, i would refuse to run against him. Like that saying in the Days of Thunder movie, He hit everyone but the pace car. From the drop of the green flag, he was on the outside and immediatly turned left when someone was right beside him, he forced that guy off the trac just 2 seconds into the race. He proceeded to hit everyone in front of him and beside him. Looks like you all would get tired of that. I did see a few people take a stab back at him and one kart took him up to the top of the track 2 times thru the race as to teach him a lesson but he stopped short of taking him completely out, but he didnt learn, he came right back down and hit everyone else, alot of guys starting pushing him back. Then the #21 had the outragousness to get mad and ram a stopped kart that was waiting to get on the scales. Then he gets mad off the track at someone else and i guess his dad did to. They need to bar #21 from the trac completely before he hurts someone. He is not a good racer, even if he wins one every now and then. He dont know how to drive with finness. I wish that kart that took him up to the top of the track to teach him a lesson would have dumped him off the other side. I've been racing for 4 years and have never seen anything like that. I heard they barred him from the track, but i don't know if that was for the night, a few weeks or indefinitly. I vote for the latter. I don't know who that is nor do i want to because it might then become personnal. Just a view from a spectator and racer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> speedracer</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#FF9300>(7/6/03 9:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkartanddriverfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=47.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> quite a hefty letter</span><hr size=1> I dont know who that #21 kart was either, but he is exactly what you said. He is like that week after week. By far the worst driver at Richmong. That brings up a good question. I know kart &amp; driver has had a driver of the yaer contest, but how about a unofficial:<br>
